<p>Great point. One of the things that seems to escape people with higher playtimes is that not everyone will play the game very often. I've seen a lot of informal posts where people try to track player counts with /who all 30 40, and they tend to focus on the number of players returned, not the names of the players themselves. The raw numbers at any given time are a bit low for those mid level players, but you'll notice a lot of variance in the names of characters logging in from that level range. /who all 65, or /who all 70 will yield the same names, night in, and night out.</p>

<p>I think a lot of people would still like to see LDoN get a boost in terms of equipment. With SOE implementing the option for a partial refund of adventure points when you sell back existing gear, there will be people who don't want to see the system abandoned after SOE had stated they will be making additions to it. The obvious exception would be if new LDoN style adventures in higher level zones would work off of the same point structure (something tells me this will come in the form of the next expansion though.)</p>

<p>Adding new LDoN Zones for higher levels with new faction requirements, but using the existing point system so people can get some value back trading in gear might be the best way to go.</p>

<p>More quests for gear would be a nice addition as well. Something tells me the Task system could eventually serve as a pretty nice way to replace the older quest system.</p>
