<p>Much like Scott, the reason I multi-box is so I dont spend a lot of time LFG, or having to beg for help to get something done.  This need is not driven by being anti-social.  Its driven by the fact that the amount of RL time I can commit to EQ is too limited to get anything done otherwise.</p>

<p>Sitting on my @$$ for 2-4 hours mindlessly following a raid leaders instructions so I can build up enough DKP to get some uber item is NOT my idea of a fun game.     All of my characters are level 65, and have very high-end bazaar gear and some ornate.  I have done (with my Guild) all of the alternate access PoP quests just for the charm stats and AA's.     </p>

<p>We are pretty much at a standstill in terms of character progerssion at this point, as there are no upgrades attainable by people with our playstyle that will allow us to play in GoD or the higher end OoW zones where we can get real gear upgrades.</p>

